{
 "name": "RPlog_Traitor_s_Redemption",
 "title": "Traitor's Redemption: The Execution of Sandor Woden",
 "summary": "In the transformed hangar bay of the Star Destroyer Inquisitor, the captured Imperial traitor Sandor Woden is paraded before assembled Stormtroopers, the Royal Guard, SAGed students, and the Navy for a public execution broadcast galaxy-wide by IGN correspondent Timo Droja. Tortured and resigned, Sandor faces the crowd whose belief system he abandoned for the love of the late Ai'kani, and when the ISB agent Dreven reads the charges of treason, he pleads guilty on all counts, seeking a clean death. As officers and observers--Krieg, Wolf, Vextin Mandor, Captain DeVilliers, the disguised Royal Guard Arissa, and the bloodthirsty student Ashden--watch with varied unease and relish, Dreven executes Sandor with an antique ballistic pistol. The body is bagged and spirited away aboard a waiting COMPNOR shuttle, and Dreven presses the spent bullet casing into Ashden's hand as a grim souvenir before the assembly disperses.",
